cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SAL — Saccade Analysis Lab"
message: "If you use SAL in academic work, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Masih
    family-names: Shafiei
    email: shafiei.masih@gmail.com
    affiliation: "Thier Lab, Hertie Institute for Clinical Brain Research, University of Tübingen"
abstract: >-
  SAL (Saccade Analysis Lab) is a MATLAB toolkit for detecting and analyzing
  saccades (rapid eye movements) from time series of eye-position data
  acquired with search-coil or video-based eye trackers. Its core
  saccade-detection method builds on the adaptive velocity-threshold
  principle of Nyström and Holmqvist (2010), using fixation-period noise
  levels to define data-driven thresholds.
repository-code: "https://github.com/shafiei-masih/SAL"
license: MIT
